div.p:
It is infinite patience that the Lord bears with any of us. The Angels sinned but once, and they were cast out of Heaven.
• dam sinned but once, and was cast out of Paradise;
wee have multiplied transgressions, and yet behold wee live. Admire the riches of Gods patience, and let it lead us to repentance, else that God which slew Elah in the act of his sin, may also slay thee; hee that slew Zimri and Cozbi in the act of uncleaanness, if thou act such wickedness, may slay thee; hee that made the Earth to devour Corah, and his followers, for their opposing Moses and Aaron, will not alwaies bear with our revilers of Magistracy and Ministery.

Yea further, I say, the Lord God lay it not to their charge,
who have said that I did it in malice, devilishness, and envy;
it is the desire of my soul that they might bee saved,
